  "articleSummary": "The article **\"Your Laptop Is the Breach\"** argues that modern developer laptops have become high-value targets for attackers due to their role as centralized repositories of sensitive credentials and infrastructure access. The core thesis is that routine user actions—like opening a PDF, clicking an SMS link, or installing a tool—can escalate into full breaches when laptops store unsecured credentials (e.g., SSH keys, `.env` files, cloud CLI configs, AI tool contexts) and backups. The tone is urgent and analytical, framing the laptop as a \"credential warehouse\" and emphasizing that attackers exploit mundane, \"boring\" vectors (phishing, fake CAPTCHAs,",
